{
  "texts": [
    "These methods are discussed in terms of separate training, joint training, and multi-modal generative retrieval.",
    "SeparateTraining.",
    "For fact verification tasks [284], which involve determining the correctness of input claims, GERE [27] proposed using an encoder-decoder-based GR model to replace traditional indexing-based methods.",
    "Specifically, GERE first utilizes a claim encoder to encode input claims, and then generates document titles related to the claim through a title decoder to obtain candidate sentences for corresponding documents.Knowledge-Intensive Language Tasks.",
    "For Knowledge-Intensive Language Tasks (KILT) [218], CorpusBrain [28] introduced three pre-training tasks to enhance the model's understanding of query-document relationships at various granularities: Internal Sentence Selection, Leading Paragraph Selection, and Hyperlink Identifier Prediction."
  ]
}